  "elapsed_s": 9.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But was the name of this barge. and they went-- the went down through [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] the sea, to Constanza, to Sulina.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Sulina is this town that, then you reach the Red Sea.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they waited there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The owners of the-- [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] what was the name of the ship? of the pressured, you go, go [INAUDIBLE] still no ships, there.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I found out, now, that Mr.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Rand had taken and stolen these 2,000 pounds-- had taken for himself, and tried to get this Turkish ship to get there without any money.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He succeeded in getting them there, but now they wanted money.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they wanted the permission to leave-- they are, all the time, they hope that they would get permission from the British, to leave.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were very uninformed about the whole situation.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I made a contract.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I couldn't get into Turkey, into Romania at that time, because the British had succeeded, in Romania, to put a arrest order on me.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So I had to stay in Hungary.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I sent a woman, a Viennese woman, who was a British citizen-- she had married a Viennese guy, who was born in 1914, when the Austrians were [? entered ?] from the Isle of Man, I believe, they were [? entered ?].",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And she was born-- he was born in British territory, therefore he was a British citizen.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Before she married him, she had a British passport, which enabled her to travel freely.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And she was a very clever, very energetic, but highly hysterical woman.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Well, we got a treaty with these Turks, with these Turks, that we made, with them, four trips or five trips.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
